At the end of this course:
the student is familiar with the basic concepts, such as topology, open and closed sets, and continuous functions, and is able to use these to prove some fundamental results;
the student knows several ways to define a topology on a set and can compare different topologies on the same set;
the student can determine if a given topological space satisfies certain properties (such as compactness and connectedness);
